Big fan of this dish and it's big enough for 2 people. We ordered at peak dinner time so it took about an hour to be delivered. The driver was courteous and the food was hot like it was just made. They do a good job of packaging their food. The chicken had a nice crispy breading and was served in sweet and spicy sauce. I will say all of the sauces seem to be more on the sweet side and it tends to make the chicken soggy after a while. Next time I would get it on the side. Fried rice was tasty and not to salty. They have really good egg rolls as well. We will order from again.

And so, too baffled to reject the already opened drink, I had the first beer on ice of my entire life. We got our meals to go just to get away from the eerie atmosphere of the desolate place. The quality of food was decent, but the feeling of unease followed us back to the hotel.

I was told I would be refunded for the kung pao shrimp (which was requested not spicy and only contained 6 pieces of shrimp). Never received a refund. Super disappointing experience on several levels. We won't be back.

Was driving into downtown St Louis from an hour away and had my daughter phone in an order for pickup since they were closing soon and we needed food to take back to our hotel after starving all day. The lady on the phone was very nice and took the order then repeated the order back to my daughter. I heard the order being placed and heard her repeat the order. Picked up the order 30 minutes before they closed, got back to the hotel, parked and went up to our room. Upon getting the food out, found out they completely skipped my daughters food. Called the restaurant 15 minutes before closing time and was hoping they would deliver her food since it was their mistake. Lady refused to deliver it, kept saying she didn't charge me for it. I explained I'd happily pay for it, but my daughter needed food. She refused to make it, deliver it, or anything at all. Just kept arguing that she didn't charge me for it. Will never even consider this place again. Rangoons were like rubber with no flavor and the Chili Oil Beef was like processed beef with no flavor. I expected better, but I'll go back home and get decent Chinese food for a lot less.
